Rangers are based out of Hibernia, a land of the fae and magical. <br>
Scouts are Albion, which is pretty much medieval England with a few twists. <br>
<br>
Scouts get to use the Longbow, which has the best range in the game.<br>
Rangers get access to a selfbuff line of spells and dual-wield.<br>
<br>
In Albion, Scouts are the best pullers in the realm.  Bar none. Merc's and Armsmen will on occassion pretend to pull, but most will relinquish the position readily to a scout. <br>
<br>
I can't really speak to rangers as I'm not playing a character in Hibernia.  <br>
